  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight based on the discovered failures: it characterizes properties of the failures (counts of error-inducing inputs, number/diversity of misclassified labels, success rate, and an inactivation-rate analysis) and demonstrates that the discovered failures can be used to fine-tune and improve model accuracy. However, it does not perform diagnostic analysis that traces failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., dataset bias, spurious features, corrupt training data, or detailed internal neuron/feature attribution). The paper's explanation that CNNs are susceptible to \"continuous perturbations\" is presented as the method's motivating insight (methodology), not as an analysis of the discovered failures themselves; thus the work stops short of linking the observed errors to concrete root causes inside the model or dataset.",
